1 Preheat the oven to 400Â°F
2 Take the pizza bread from the fridge and let warm on the counter
3 Cut up a hot dog/sausage into half inch slices
4 Cut up a green bell pepper into bite-sized chunks
5 Cut up a few mushrooms (enough for a pizza)
6 Again pour some oil into a non-stick frying pan
7 Heat the oil over medium heat
8 Fry the mushrooms slices in the skillet
9 Put enough ketchup on the pizza crust to thinly cover it
10 Place the hot dog/sausage slices, green bell pepper slices, and fried mushrooms on the pizza.
11 Add enough shredded mozzarella cheese to cover the pizza
12 Place the pizza in the pre-heated oven for 20 minutes
13 Remove the pizza and let it cool on the counter
